name: MT4CSVData
doc:
Parses a `Metatrader4 <https://www.metaquotes.net/en/metatrader4>`_ History
center CSV exported file.

Specific parameters (or specific meaning):

  - ``dataname``: The filename to parse or a file-like object

  - Uses GenericCSVData and simply modifies the params

methods.name: _add2stack
methods.doc: Saves given bar (list of values) to the stack for later retrieval

methods.name: _fromstack
methods.doc:
Load a value from the stack onto the lines to form the new bar

Returns True if values are present, False otherwise

methods.name: _getnexteos
methods.doc: Returns the next eos using a trading calendar if available

methods.name: _gettz
methods.doc:
To be overriden by subclasses which may auto-calculate the
timezone

methods.name: _gettzinput
methods.doc: Can be overriden by classes to return a timezone for input

methods.name: _operation_stage1
methods.doc:
Two operands' operation. Scanning of other happens to understand
if other must be directly an operand or rather a subitem thereof

methods.name: _operation_stage2
methods.doc:
Rich Comparison operators. Scans other and returns either an
operation with other directly or a subitem from other

methods.name: _operationown_stage1
methods.doc: Operation with single operand which is "self"

methods.name: _roperation
methods.doc:
Relies on self._operation to and passes "r" True to define a
reverse operation

methods.name: _save2stack
methods.doc:
Saves current bar to the bar stack for later retrieval

Parameter ``erase`` determines removal from the data stream

methods.name: _updatebar
methods.doc:
Load a value from the stack onto the lines to form the new bar

Returns True if values are present, False otherwise

methods.name: addminperiod
methods.doc: The passed minperiod is fed to the lines

methods.name: compensate
methods.doc:
Call it to let the broker know that actions on this asset will
compensate open positions in another

methods.name: get_notifications
methods.doc: Return the pending "store" notifications

methods.name: incminperiod
methods.doc: The passed minperiod is fed to the lines

methods.name: islive
methods.doc:
If this returns True, ``Cerebro`` will deactivate ``preload`` and
``runonce`` because a live data source must be fetched tick by tick (or
bar by bar)

methods.name: minbuffer
methods.doc: Receive notification of how large the buffer must at least be

methods.name: next
methods.doc: Called to calculate values when the minperiod is over

methods.name: nextstart
methods.doc:
It will be called when the minperiod phase is over for the 1st
post-minperiod value. Only called once and defaults to automatically
calling next

methods.name: once
methods.doc: Called to calculate values at "once" when the minperiod is over

methods.name: oncestart
methods.doc:
It will be called when the minperiod phase is over for the 1st
post-minperiod value

Only called once and defaults to automatically calling once

methods.name: prenext
methods.doc: It will be called during the "minperiod" phase of an iteration.

methods.name: preonce
methods.doc: It will be called during the "minperiod" phase of a "once" iteration

methods.name: put_notification
methods.doc: Add arguments to notification queue

methods.name: qbuffer
methods.doc: Change the lines to implement a minimum size qbuffer scheme

methods.name: setenvironment
methods.doc: Keep a reference to the environment

methods.name: setminperiod
methods.doc:
Direct minperiod manipulation. It could be used for example
by a strategy
to not wait for all indicators to produce a value

methods.name: updateminperiod
methods.doc:
Update the minperiod if needed. The minperiod will have been
calculated elsewhere
and has to take over if greater that self's

alias.doc:
Built-in immutable sequence.

If no argument is given, the constructor returns an empty tuple.
If iterable is specified the tuple is initialized from iterable's items.

If the argument is a tuple, the return value is the same object.

aliased.doc:
str(object='') -> str
str(bytes_or_buffer[, encoding[, errors]]) -> str

Create a new string object from the given object. If encoding or
errors is specified, then the object must expose a data buffer
that will be decoded using the given encoding and error handler.
Otherwise, returns the result of object.__str__() (if defined)
or repr(object).
encoding defaults to sys.getdefaultencoding().
errors defaults to 'strict'.

lines.doc:
Defines an "array" of lines which also has most of the interface of
a LineBuffer class (forward, rewind, advance...).

This interface operations are passed to the lines held by self

The class can autosubclass itself (_derive) to hold new lines keeping them
in the defined order.
